Badan Gruk	A Dal Honese sergeant commanding the 5th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. Short, broad, and very dark-skinned, with pronounced epicanthic folds and a habitually unsmiling expression, he is well suited to disappearing in darkness and prefers the safety of moonless nights. He followed Sinter, a woman from his own tribe, into the Malazan military despite having little interest in fighting for its own sake. Practical, survival-minded, and deeply aware of danger, he carries a traditional Dal Honese vethbela: a two-handed sickle sword of carved tusk set with thin otataral blades.<br>
Beak	A Quon Talian human mage serving with the Bonehunters, likely in the 8th Legion, 9th Company. Guileless, nervous, and almost childlike in thought and manner, he often appears with a gawking expression or wide smile and considers himself foolish despite extraordinary magical talent. Sorcery is the one field he understands deeply: he conceives of warrens as coloured candles and is accomplished in every warren. A skilled rider from a horse-breeding background, he joins the Malazan military seeking a place among people like himself, though his awkward honesty and anxious talk of magic leave many fellow soldiers unsettled.<br>
Bellig Harn	A heavy infantry soldier in the Malazan 14th Army, serving in the 8th Legion, 9th Company, 12th Squad under Sergeant Thom Tiss. He is counted among the Bonehunters and associated with the hard-used infantry formations that support the marines during major campaigns. His squad includes soldiers such as Tulip, Ramp, Jibb, Gullstream, and Mudslinger, placing him within one of the compact, close-knit units that define the Bonehunters' field structure.<br>
Bivatt	A Letherii Atri-Preda, equivalent to a Malazan Fist, commanding the Drene Garrison of the Eastern Letherii Army. Though she works alongside Drene's Factor, Letur Anict, her first duty is to the Letherii Empire. Militarily confident and hard-edged, she is prepared to do whatever she considers necessary to win and does not rely on moral justifications for warfare. Most consider her a likely future Preda of the Imperial Armies, marking her as one of Lether's more prominent field commanders.<br>
Brethless	A Malazan marine in the Bonehunters and twin brother of Touchy. Originally a city guard in Kartool's Septarch District under Sergeant Hellian, he serves as joint corporal with Touchy in Hellian's 8th Squad. The twins are not considered especially bright, cannot swim, and often answer orders in tandem, worsening Hellian's drunken belief that they are a single four-armed corporal. The younger twin by a few minutes, he insists those minutes were crucial to his superior mental development.<br>
Brevity	A short, dark-haired ex-con at Second Maiden Fort who becomes a self-styled inspector and port authority alongside her partner Pithy. Practical, opportunistic, and faintly absurd in official manner, she helps inspect ships and charge anchoring fees in the harbour. She knows Skorgen Kaban by reputation and is credulous enough to have once paid for a dubious relic supposedly connected to him, a detail that underlines the comic, rough-edged character of Second Maiden Fort's improvised authorities.<br>
Brohl Handar	A Tiste Edur of the Arapay tribe, minor noble of the Letherii Empire, and newly appointed Overseer of the East in Drene. Formerly patriarch of a seal-hunting clan, he has little experience with government and does not consider himself sophisticated. In Drene he occupies a nominally powerful post, though real authority rests with Factor Letur Anict and the Liberty Consign. Like many traditional Edur, Brohl struggles to understand Letherii hunger for gold and material wealth, and his role places him uneasily between imperial duty, Edur custom, and Letherii corruption.<br>
Brullyg|Shake	A full-blooded Shake, pretender to the Shake throne, and self-declared ruler of Second Maiden Fort. Formerly imprisoned for murder before the Tiste Edur invasion freed him, he is ambitious, intelligent, and difficult to kill, with heavy brows, a flabby neck, and skill in several languages including Shake, Letherii, Tiste Edur, Fent, trader's tongue, Meckros, and some Malazan. Shurq Elalle knows him from earlier dealings and considers him completely mad. He imagines a renewed Shake power centred on the island, mixing crude opportunism with genuine political ambition.<br>
Bruthen Trana	A tall, grey-skinned Tiste Edur of the Den-Ratha tribe who serves Emperor Rhulad Sengar as liaison to the Patriotists in Letheras. One of the few Edur living in the Eternal Domicile, he is a lifelong warrior rather than a courtier, wearing a leather cloak and sword belt and carrying little of wealth. His position requires regular dealings with Karos Invictad's Patriotists, an arrangement that leaves him exposed to Letherii obstruction and palace intrigue. Sullen, dutiful, and increasingly wary, he is concerned by the Emperor's isolation from his family and people.<br>
Drawfirst	A heavy infantry soldier in Primly's 10th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. She has the red hair and blue eyes associated with Falari ancestry, along with the olive-hued skin of the indigenous Walk population of the Falari Isles. Bonehunter soldiers group her with the heavies Lookback and Shoaly as supposed cousins because of their similar appearance and heritage, though the three did not know one another before enlistment.<br>
Emroth	A broken T'lan Imass of the Unbound, one of the Teblor gods known as the Seven Faces in the Rock. Her name means Fanged Skeleton, and the Teblor call her Imroth the Cruel; the Rathyd clan worship her as patron goddess and burn blood on the stone lips of her effigy to set curses on enemies. Once of the Eptr Phinana clan of the Kron T'lan Imass, she is also a Soletaken of unknown form. Her damaged face and ancient flint weapon give her a severe, ominous presence.<br>
Gr'istanas Ish'ilm	A T'lan Imass Bonecaster of the Bentract, also spelled Gr'istanas Ish'Ilm. He wears rotted clothes and possesses a Soletaken form resembling a large bear with long legs, a vestigial tail, black and brown hair, and a flattened snout. His presence links the Refugium's Bentract Imass to the deeper, older traditions of Imass bonecasters and shapeshifting power.<br>
Gunth Mach	A young K'Chain Che'Malle Drone who serves as one of Redmask's bodyguards alongside the K'ell Hunter Sag'Churok. In the process of growing into a female, she has dark-hued skin, balances on two massive hind legs, and bears deadly talons on her forelegs. Swift, predatory, and ravenous, she often hunts with Sag'Churok; rhinazan from Lether's eastern Wastelands follow her and perch on her back to clean ticks and blood from her scales.<br>
Hadralt	War leader of the Ganetok, the most powerful of the remaining Awl clans, and also leader over remnants of the Niritha and Sevond clans. The firstborn son and successor of Capalah, he is dark-eyed, lean, and short, carrying his father's swagger without the same physical authority. Reputedly very fast with the hook-bladed shortswords he wears cross-strapped beneath his arms, he surrounds himself with favoured hulking warriors known as Copperfaces and wears a belt lined with fetishes.<br>
Hanno	A heavy infantry soldier in Sergeant Sobelone's squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malazan 14th Army. He is listed among the Bonehunters' heavy troops, the durable infantry who support the army's marine elements and give the 14th much of its staying power in the field.<br>
Hanradi Khalag	A Tiste Edur warlock and chief of the Merude tribe on Lether. The Merude are the strongest of the six Edur clans, with a vast population and tens of thousands of warriors, making Hanradi a major tribal leader. He has won more trophies for his belt than any warrior in generations, and his skill with a spear is greater than his power as a warlock. Older in appearance, with a weathered face, hunched shoulders, and raspy voice, he embodies the martial authority of traditional Edur leadership.<br>
Honey	A sapper in Pravalak Rim's 4th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. He has a history of directing unwanted affection toward female soldiers around him, with Skim noted as his current object of attention and Kisswhere also catching his eye. His role as a sapper places him among the Malazan soldiers responsible for explosives, breaching work, and the dangerous practical craft associated with munitions.<br>
Hostille Rator	A clan chief of the Bentract T'lan Imass, named to that position by Bentract himself. He has a mottled, scarred pate with filthy long hair knotted with calcified bones, and a dominant brow ridge that buries his eyes in darkness. Dressed in rotted clothes, he fights with a cutlass-length obsidian sword in one hand and a bone-hafted groundstone maul in the other, presenting an ancient and formidable Imass warrior's aspect.<br>
Hunt	A Kartoolian corporal in Primly's 10th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. His rank places him as the squad's immediate junior leader under Sergeant Primly, part of the Malazan 14th Army's compact marine structure during the Bonehunters' campaigns.<br>
Janath Anar	A Letherii scholar and former senior lecturer at the Academy of Imperial Learning in Letheras. She specialises in the psychology of the human mind, with lectures and papers concerned with personal responsibility, the necessity of compassion, and the rejection of moral relativism. Her intellectual work marks her as a moral and analytical voice within Letherii academic life, focused on the ethical dimensions of human behaviour.<br>
K'risnan	Also called the K'risnan Cadre, the K'risnan are Hannan Mosag's five apprentices in sorcery. They are the young firstborn sons of subjugated Tiste Edur chiefs, held as hostages after the War of Unification to secure the Warlock King's control over the tribes. Their true names are stripped away, their new names chosen privately and bound with spells, and their shaved heads mark their sundering from their fathers' bloodlines. Trained at Mosag's side, they are intended to become future chiefs loyal to him.<br>
Karos Invictad	A Letherii human and Invigilator of the Patriotists, the state security force of the Letherii Empire. Considered the most powerful man in the empire after Emperor Rhulad Sengar, he is served by Tanal Yathvanar as personal assistant. Pudgy, high-voiced, and fond of crimson silks, rings, onyx, and other finery, Karos presents his authority through both luxury and menace, including a black bloodwood sceptre concealing a knife. He considers himself exceptionally intelligent, collects difficult mechanical puzzles, and writes cold treatises on compulsion and control.<br>
Kilmandaros	An Elder Goddess worshipped by the Forkrul Assail. She favours a form with Forkrul Assail-like traits, including more joints than a normal humanoid body, allowing her to contort herself into strange shapes. Associated with destruction and desecration, she carries the terrible weight of an elder power whose interests and nature are far removed from ordinary mortal concerns.<br>
Letur Anict	A high-ranking member of the Liberty Consign of Merchants and Factor in Drene. Although Brohl Handar is officially Overseer, real power in the city rests with the Factor. Pale-skinned, with a strangely round face, light blue eyes, and nearly white pallid blond hair, he is a silk-robed bureaucratic mind who prides himself on numbers. Precise, controlling, and intolerant of deviation, he treats every insult as grievous and every failure as an insult, maintaining spies, agents, and poison-skilled assassins throughout Drene and the Eastern Army.<br>
Lookback	A heavy infantry soldier in Sergeant Sinter's 4th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. He has the red hair and blue eyes common to Falari ancestry, together with the olive-hued skin of the indigenous Walk population of the Falari Isles. Bonehunter soldiers think of him, Drawfirst, and Shoaly as cousins because of their similar appearance and heritage, though the three did not know one another before joining the army. He often takes point when his squad is on the move.<br>
Madan'tul Rada	Malazan lieutenant of the 14th Army serving under Captain Faradan Sort around the time of the Last Siege of Y'Ghatan in Seven Cities. Sort finds his name a mouthful but generally appreciates his taciturn nature. He carries a round shield, fitting his role as a practical field officer within the Bonehunters' command structure.<br>
Masarch	The young Awl war leader of the once-mighty Renfayar clan. He and five other youths are all that remain of the clan's warriors as the Renfayar border on extinction. Having cast off old ways that served them poorly, they have not undergone the traditional ritual marking the passage to adulthood. He wears a hide jerkin and stands as a stark emblem of a clan reduced to desperate youth and fragile continuity.<br>
Mayfly	A heavy infantry soldier in Sergeant Mosel's squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malazan 14th Army. Easily confused but extraordinarily tough, she has broken her nose more times than she can count and finds the clicking sounds of setting it vaguely satisfying. Her blunt soldierly outlook treats too much thinking as a hindrance to fighting, making her a rough, durable example of Malazan heavy infantry pragmatism.<br>
Mulvan Dreader	A Nathii squad mage in Primly's 10th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. Pale-skinned and black-haired, he specialises in combat magic but can perform healing when necessary. Beak identifies him as a Nathii swamp necromancer, placing his sorcery in a distinct regional and practical tradition. Among his squadmates, he is observant enough to remark on Skulldeath's strained celibacy.<br>
Natarkas	A large, well-muscled Awl warrior of the Ganetok clan and a member of the Copperfaces. The Copperfaces cover their faces with reddish copper-coloured pigment in imitation of Redmask's red-scaled mask, honouring the exploits of the Awl exile they admire. He belongs to the trusted inner circle of close companions surrounding Hadralt, the Ganetok war leader.<br>
Neller	A Dal Honese sapper in Primly's 10th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. As a sapper, he belongs to the Malazan military tradition of soldiers trusted with explosives, breaching work, and dangerous practical ingenuity within the squad structure.<br>
Nep Furrow	A Dal Honese bush shaman and mage in Badan Gruk's 5th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. Wrinkled, yellow-eyed, and dark-faced, with gnarled hands and piercings through ears, nose, wattle, and cheeks, he wears gold ornaments that stand out sharply against his scowling features. Bottle thinks his eyes still have the jungle in them, and his accent is so thick that many of his utterances are nearly unintelligible.<br>
Nimander Golit	A young Tiste Andii and first son of Anomander Rake. Tall, with long white hair the colour of starlight, he once lived on the moving island of Drift Avalii with his uncle Andarist and other Tiste Andii protectors of the Throne of Shadow. He wears a heavy dark blue woollen cloak and privately imagines his modest sword skills as those of a heroic defender of Mother Dark, though he is more capable with a blade than he believes.<br>
Old Hunch Arbat	A Tarthenal shaman living near Breeder's Wood in the Kingdom of Lether, among the few of his race still found within a day's walk of the place. He collects refuse from Tarthenal Indebted farms while mixed-blood children mock him and throw rotten fruit. Huge, gnarled hands, a bristly prognathous jaw, blackened teeth from Letherii sweet-cakes, and the stink of his daily work mark his appearance. He talks to himself and often refers to himself in the third person.<br>
Orbyn Truthfinder	Section Commander of the Patriotists and the most feared man in Drene. Huge, fat, and physically softened by years of inactivity, he has a fleshy face, small eyes set between folds of fat, thin lips and brows, a wattle, and slack jowls. He sweats constantly, gives off an acrid smell, and dislikes the feel of soft earth beneath him. Overseer Brohl Handar considers him among the most despicable and malicious people he has ever met.<br>
Phaed	A young Tiste Andii who lives on the moving island of Drift Avalii as one of the youthful protectors of the Throne of Shadow. Granddaughter of Anomander Rake, she has a flat, heart-shaped face, skin the colour of smudged slate, white hair, and a beauty marked by a dazzling smile and natural glamour that can leave new acquaintances breathless. Like others among Rake's kin on Drift Avalii, she does not seem especially familiar with arms or weaponry.<br>
Pithy	A tall, thin, pale ex-thief from Second Maiden Fort who becomes a self-styled inspector and port authority with her partner Brevity. She has stringy blonde hair and says she was born on the island, suggesting she is the child of one of its prisoners. Her improvised official role gives Second Maiden Fort's harbour authority a comic, dubious edge, blending criminal pasts with makeshift governance.<br>
Pravalak Rim	Corporal of Sinter's 4th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. The youngest son of poor farmers in a northern province of Gris, he was a sheltered country boy until a beautiful middle-aged Dal Honese marine recruiter drew him into the Malazan military. Haunted, romantic, and susceptible to powerful infatuations, he sheds whatever innocence he brought from home into the rough intimacy of army life.<br>
Primly	A young Quon Talian sergeant commanding the 10th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. He has a long, ascetic face with little beard and a sour expression when addressed. Formerly a Quon noble, he committed some act that left him disowned and possibly on the run, but his time in the Malazan army stripped away any remaining highborn airs.<br>
Pully	A Shake witch, or shoulderwoman, serving as a housemaid at Boaral Keep alongside Skwish. Yan Tovis describes both women as hags, and this witch is marked by wrinkled brows and knobby, hairy feet with taloned toes. Among Letherii her speech becomes less refined, dropping letters and joining words together, though this shifts according to whom she recognises. She also has a nephew who once dug latrines for the Grass Jackets Brigade.<br>
Rautos Hivanar	Head of an old-money Letherii family and Master of the Liberty Consign of Merchants in Letheras. Said to be the wealthiest man in the empire, he is large, florid, robust-featured, and dominant in any room he enters. Busy with the Consign and his family's vast financial holdings, he regards the Tiste Edur conquerors with contempt. His trusted steward and principal agent is Venitt Sathad, whose family has been Indebted to the Hivanars for six generations and who operates with broad authority in his master's name.<br>
Redmask	An Awl exile returned to the Awl'dan, the traditional homeland of his people, to make war on the Letherii. His name comes from the full-face red-scaled mask with black-rimmed eye slits that he always wears. Short, lithe, and wiry, he wears a scaled hauberk beneath a rodara-wool shirt and rough hooded cloak. A master of legendary Awl weapons, the cadaran whip and rygtha crescent axe, he is a brutal fighter, skilled rider, and knowledgeable observer of Awl'dan politics and Letherii military formations.<br>
Reem	A corporal serving under Sergeant Sobelone in the heavy infantry of the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malazan 14th Army. Direct and plain-spoken, he is shown cutting through elaborate explanations to state the blunt practical fact of a situation, a quality well suited to the Bonehunters' hard-bitten soldierly culture.<br>
Reliko	A Dal Honese heavy infantry soldier in Badan Gruk's 5th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. Short, ebon-skinned, and with almost no neck, he is so small that Braven Tooth reportedly calls him the smallest heavy infantryman in Malazan imperial history. He carries a shortsword and shield and keeps watch over Vastly Blank, ensuring his thickheaded squadmate does not misplace his weapon or forget the enemy.<br>
Rhulad	A handsome Tiste Edur of House Sengar and the fourth and youngest son of Tomad and Uruth. Brother to Fear, Trull, and the mage Binadas, he begins as a brash, unsubtle, unblooded young warrior eager to prove himself before his tribe and impress others. Indulged by his elder brothers, he has clear grey eyes and a tendency to mistake Trull's reluctance to fight for weakness. His childhood companion Midik Buhn often practices swordplay with him.<br>
Ruffle	A soldier in Badan Gruk's 5th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. Pale-skinned, grey-eyed, and nearly round without yet sagging, she is not someone Badan Gruk considers naturally suited for promotion, though he notes her cool eye when she is not busy eating everything in sight. She also likes to smoke rustleaf.<br>
Sag'Churok	A hulking male K'Chain Che'Malle K'ell Hunter who serves as one of Redmask's bodyguards alongside Gunth Mach. He has a sinuous neck, a broad jaw filled with dagger-like fangs, enormous hind legs with taloned feet, and a huge tail held straight back for balance. Instead of hands, his heavily muscled arms end in great curved iron swords. Predatory and ravenous, he can make enormous leaps and bring down prey far larger than an ox.<br>
Saltlick	Also called Salty, a heavy infantryman in the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malazan 14th Army, likely serving in either Sergeant Sobelone's or Sergeant Tugg's heavy infantry squad. He has a massive round face usually fixed in a cow-like expression of uninterested incomprehension. His rough physicality and dull-seeming manner make him a memorable example of the Bonehunters' heavies.<br>
Sandalath Drukorlat	Also called Sand, an ancient Tiste Andii spirit. Tall as an Edur, with midnight skin, green tilted eyes, and a reddish glint in her long unbound hair, she has a face that seems too soft and round for her height and long limbs. She is dressed in leather harness and leggings with the skin of a white-furred beast on her shoulder. Linked to an unnamed husband and daughter, she describes herself as a poor fighter.<br>
Scant	A heavy infantry soldier of the 8th Legion's 9th Company in the Malazan 14th Army. He likely belongs to either Sergeant Sobelone's or Sergeant Tugg's squad, placing him among the Bonehunters' hard-used heavy infantry formations.<br>
Shoaly	A heavy infantry soldier in Sergeant Sinter's 4th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. He has the red hair and blue eyes common to Falari ancestry, together with the olive-hued skin of the indigenous Walk population of the Falari Isles, and he is fond of Flashwit. Bonehunter soldiers think of him, Drawfirst, and Lookback as cousins because of their similar appearance and heritage, though the three did not know one another before enlistment.<br>
Sirryn Kanar	Sergeant of the Guard of the Eternal Domicile during Emperor Rhulad Sengar's reign, a lieutenant in the Palace Cell of the Patriotists, and personal bodyguard to Chancellor Triban Gnol. Born in Letheras, he has flat, remorseless eyes and a household he is pleased to keep in fear. A wholehearted believer in Karos Invictad, he embraces Patriotist certainty, authority, and suspicion, fearing what he does not understand and despising what he fears. He detests the Tiste Edur and treats mercy toward enemies as weakness.<br>
Skim	A sapper in Badan Gruk's 5th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. She is one of the women subjected to Honey's unwanted affections and regularly warns him to stop calling her beloved. Sharp enough to complain about practical squad problems, she notes that Badan Gruk's dark skin and preference for moonless nights can make him vanish into the dark just when his soldiers need him.<br>
Skorgen Kaban|Skorgen the Pretty	A Letherii sailor also known as Skorgen the Pretty, serving as Shurq Elalle's first mate aboard the Undying Gratitude. Battered by misfortune, he has one good eye, one working ear, blackened teeth, a prodigious gut, a ruined hawkish nose reduced to gaping nostrils and sensitive scar tissue, a stump for one arm, and a limp from a bad leg. Religious and superstitious, he prays to dangerous sea spirits, performs warding gestures, and possesses unusual knowledge of Tiste Edur culture. Despite chronic pain and awkward movement, he can be quick when needed.<br>
Skulldeath	Formerly Tribole Futan, the last surviving male of the Futani royal line of the Gilani tribe of southeast Seven Cities. A twenty-three-year-old marine in Primly's 10th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters, he is not tall but is extremely strong, all muscle and no fat, with dark almond-shaped eyes considered feminine. Quiet and shy-smiling, he fights in the Gilani style with two great tulwars once owned by his great-uncle, a Falah'dan champion. His name was given by Braven Tooth in Malaz City.<br>
Skwish	A Shake witch, or shoulderwoman, serving as a housemaid at Boaral Keep alongside Pully. Yan Tovis describes both women as hags, and this witch has wrinkled brows and knobby, hairy feet with taloned toes. Among Letherii her vocabulary becomes less refined, with dropped letters and contracted words, though her speech shifts according to circumstance and recognition.<br>
Strap Mull	A Dal Honese sapper in the 4th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. His place among the sappers marks him as one of the Malazan soldiers trusted with explosives, breaching work, and the hazardous practical craft that often defines the army's most dangerous operations.<br>
Tanal Yathvanar	Assistant to Karos Invictad, Invigilator of the Letherii Patriotists. A fervent believer in the Patriotists' mission, he sees Karos as the empire's last true hope for a renewed Letherii age without Tiste Edur conquerors or subject peoples. Told since childhood that he was destined for greatness, he abandons youthful dreams of heroic freedom for authoritarian certainty. As a Patriotist officer he wears dagger and shortsword with satisfaction, savouring the authority denied to most Letherii civilians.<br>
Thom Tiss	Thom Tissy, a sergeant and medium infantryman of the 12th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malazan 14th Army. Virtually hairless, with pocked cheeks, wart-covered hands, dark beady eyes, calloused hands, and short bandy legs, he is squat as an ogre and hardly conventionally handsome. His characteristic expression of disapproval makes him look like a man who has just swallowed a Nacht turd.<br>
Til'aras Benok	A T'lan Imass Bonecaster of the Bentract, also spelled Til'Aras Benok. He wears rotted clothes and possesses a Soletaken form resembling a large bear with long legs, a vestigial tail, black and brown hair, and a flattened snout. His role as Bonecaster places him among the elder magical and spiritual figures of the Bentract Imass.<br>
Torrent	A cocky young Awl warrior who follows Redmask after the exile returns to lead his tribesmen against the Letherii. He initially wears red face paint as a sign of solidarity with Redmask, but has to abandon the practice after it gives him a rash. His youthful bravado and imitative loyalty place him among the Awl drawn to Redmask's defiant return.<br>
Tulip	A huge corporal in Sergeant Thom Tissy's 12th Squad medium infantry, 8th Legion, 9th Company of the Malazan 14th Army. His rank and size mark him as a notable presence within the Bonehunters' infantry structure, serving directly under Tissy in one of the army's squad-level formations.<br>
Vastly Blank	An oversized Seti heavy in Badan Gruk's 5th Squad, 8th Legion, 3rd Company of the Bonehunters. He does nothing to dispel the idea that heavies are mindless muscle: he barely remembers events from day to day, loses weapons and equipment unless they are secured to him, fills conversational gaps with blank stares and a slow laugh, and is chiefly interested in knowing whom he is supposed to kill. Reliko keeps an eye on him to prevent practical disasters.<br>
Venitt Sathad	House steward and principal field agent of Rautos Hivanar. His family line has been Indebted to the Hivanars for six generations, and his proven efficiency grants him wide latitude to act in his master's name without detailed oversight. Unremarkable in features and stature, with a lined face and slippers worn while working on the Hivanar estate, Venitt's plain exterior conceals a trusted and highly capable operative role within one of Letheras's wealthiest households.<br>
Wither	A shadow wraith of Tiste Andii origin enslaved by the Tiste Edur. Kettle observes him as uncommonly tall, with red eyes, and he speaks in a sibilant whisper. His existence reflects the Edur use of bound shadow spirits and gives him an eerie, half-present quality among those forced to deal with him.<br>
Yedan Derryg|The Watch	A Shake man known as The Watch, Prince and Watch of the Shake. His younger half-sister Yan Tovis, also called Twilight, is Queen of the Shake. Yedan has a prominent muscular jaw, a matted black beard, and a habit of always chewing on something. He wears a visored helmet and a chain hauberk of glistening blackened rings, and carries a long-handled single-bladed axe. Taciturn by nature, he may possess many words in his head but feels little need to give them voice.<br>
